BRADENTON â€” A 17-year-old driver was killed in the predawn hours Sunday when the car he was driving left the roadway and landed in a pond. The teenager, whose identity has not been released, was headed west on 44th Avenue E east of 19th Street Court E in Bradenton at 4:50 a.m., according to the Florida Highway Patrol. The sedan left the road and crossed a median, a sidewalk and a grassy shoulder before it overturned into a pond, coming to rest on its roof in the water, the report said. The driver was pronounced dead at the scene. The crash is under investigation, the Highway Patrol said.